Dear Colleague,

We would like to bring your attention to the (second) Call for Papers of =
the
ACCAT Workshop 2012.=20

NEWs: The paper submission deadline was extended to 23rd Dec. 2011.=20
Moreover, ACCAT now accepts also position papers.=20

We hope that you can participate in this workshop by submitting a paper
reflecting your current research.
Two types of papers are welcomed, regular papers (up to 15 pages) and
position papers (up to 8 pages).
The accepted regular papers and selected position papers will appear in
formal post-proceedings,=20
published as a volume of EPTCS. All accepted papers will appear in the =
local
proceedings of the ACCAT workshop.

Should you have any questions please don't hesitate contacting us.
On behalf of the organization team,

Thomas Soboll and Ulrike Golas.
{Apologies if you receive multiple postings}


